# Linux Network Configuration

## Commands

```bash
ip addr
ip route
ip link
hostnamectl
cat /etc/resolv.conf
```

## Purpose

### ip addr

Displays network interfaces and IP addresses.

### ip route

Displays routing table and default gateway.

### ip link

Displays interface status and MAC addresses.

### hostnamectl

Displays hostname and system information.

### /etc/resolv.conf

Contains DNS server configuration.

## Troubleshooting Steps

1. Verify interface status.
2. Check IP address.
3. Verify default gateway.
4. Confirm DNS configuration.
5. Test connectivity.
